Response_Text:
Base URL: https://api.library.com/v1

Books
MethodEndpointDescriptionGET/booksList all books (paginated)GET/books/{id}Get a specific bookPOST/booksAdd a new bookPUT/books/{id}Update book detailsDELETE/books/{id}Remove a bookGET/books/{id}/availabilityCheck copy availability
Members
MethodEndpointDescriptionPOST/membersRegister a new memberGET/members/{id}Get member profilePUT/members/{id}Update member infoDELETE/members/{id}Deactivate a member
Loans
MethodEndpointDescriptionPOST/loansIssue a book to a memberGET/loans/{id}Get loan detailsPATCH/loans/{id}/returnRecord a book returnGET/members/{id}/loansAll loans for a memberGET/loans?overdue=trueList overdue loans      Sample Request/Response // Request
{
  "member_id": "M-1042",
  "book_id": "B-9981",
  "due_date": "2026-07-13"
}

// Response 201 Created
{
  "loan_id": "L-5531",
  "member_id": "M-1042",
  "book_id": "B-9981",
  "issued_at": "2026-06-13T10:00:00Z",
  "due_date": "2026-07-13",
  "status": "active"     Error Handling
All errors follow a consistent envelope:
}           {
  "error": {
    "code": "BOOK_NOT_AVAILABLE",
    "message": "No copies of this book are currently available.",
    "status": 409
  }
}  Standard codes used: 400 (bad input), 401 (unauthenticated), 403 (unauthorized), 404 (not found), 409 (conflict — e.g., book already on loan), 429 (rate limit), 500 (server error).
Authentication via Authorization: Bearer <token> header on all write operations.
